  abstract = {A large magnetocaloric effect can be obtained around TN, Dy\textsuperimposetilde  8K simply by spinning the orthorhombic DyMnO3 single crystal within the cb-plane in a constant magnetic field, instead of the standard magnetization--demagnetization process. Under 7T, the maximum rotating entropy change (-{$\Delta$}SR, cb) and the associated adiabatic temperature change ({$\Delta$}Tad, cb) are 16.3J/kgK and 11K, respectively. The corresponding refrigerant capacity is 440J/kg, with no thermal and field hysteresis losses. Our findings show that the orthorhombic DyMnO3 could be used as a good refrigerant in more compact and efficient cryomagnetocaloric refrigerators.},
