  abstract = {Anisotropy of conventional magnetocaloric effect (MCE) and rotating magnetocaloric effect (RMCE) have been investigated in quasi-two-dimensional coordination polymer (AdeH)\textbraceleft CuII[WV(CN)8]\textbraceright{$\cdot$}2H2O with high magnetic anisotropy and topological phase transition. Magnetic entropy changes ({$\Delta$}Smag) were calculated from magnetic measurements of single crystals in three orthogonal directions, H\textbar\textbar a*, H\textbar\textbar b and H\textbar\textbar c. The highest {$\Delta$}Smag~=~3.49~J~K-1 kg-1 was recorded for conventional MCE in the H\textbar\textbar c direction for \textmu 0\textbar{$\Delta$}H\textbar =7.0~T and at a peak temperature of 37.5~K. The RMCE was calculated for the rotation around the b axis by 90{$^\circ$} from H\textbar\textbar a* to H\textbar\textbar c with the maximal {$\Delta$}Smag of 1.62~J~K-1 kg-1 detected for \textmu 0H~=~7.0~T at 38~K.},
